history.text: What do you think about Maleficent?
I enjoyed it! I thought Angelina Jolie did a really great job portraying such an interesting title character.
Yes! She is the best! I dont think Rotten Tomatoes gave her a good rating like they should have.
agreed! I was surprised to see that it had such a low rating.
Who was your favorite aside from angelinas character?
I thought Elle Fanning was great! She really embodied Aurora well. I think she's a great actress.
Who was your favorite?
I enjoyed Auroras character as well.
She portrayed it as good as the animated one.
I agree! The movie as a whole felt consistent with the original animated film :)
I love that most of the time the evil ones are really misunderstood.
yes! I found myself sympathizing a lot with Maleficient
I also enjoyed the scenery that they portrayed in this movie. It was still magical.
I agree! it really felt like we were in a fairy tale
I have to say: the movie was a lot darker than I expected it was going to be! Did you expect that it would be such a dark film?
I didnt expect it to be dark at all. It seemed like it was going to have alot more of the princess magic like feel but instead it painted a new picture of this fairy tale.
I thought the scene where Stefan cuts off Maleficient's wings was really shocking!
Yes it definitely was. It was so sad.
How about the true loves kiss. I didnt expect that..
Me neither. And I was surprised that Maleficient was initially Aurora's protector!
Yes. This is definitely a family favorite.
I don't know if I'd let young kids watch it, though-- it's really scary in parts!
If i had a choice i would choose her to be my fairy god mother
I agree! I dont have young kids so it wouldnt be a problem but i can see how it can cause nightmares.
It definitely was not a good end for stefan.
The way he fell to his own death.
Agreed!
He deserved it, though
Phillip did seem like quite the charmer.
How did you like that Maleficent was the true loves kiss?
well in motherly love .
I can see why Aurora was attracted to him!
I was surprised that she was the true loves kiss!
